14
00:00:12,028 --> 00:00:12,145
http://hiqve.c

15
00:00:12,146 --> 00:00:12,263
http://hiqve.co

16
00:00:12,264 --> 00:00:12,380
http://hiqve.com

17
00:00:12,381 --> 00:00:12,498
http://hiqve.com/

18
00:00:12,499 --> 00:00:15,499
http://hiqve.com/

19
00:00:18,523 --> 00:00:19,982
<i>Global crisis!</i>

20
00:00:20,274 --> 00:00:25,071
<i>The Mid Rim planet of Aleen is devastated
by catastrophic earthquakes.</i>

21
00:00:25,112 --> 00:00:26,614
<i>As the people struggle,</i>

22
00:00:26,656 --> 00:00:30,618
<i>the future of the survivors rests
on their ability to rekindle a way of life</i>

23
00:00:30,660 --> 00:00:32,954
<i>from the rubble of the past.</i>

24
00:00:33,037 --> 00:00:36,249
<i>A Jedi transport, on a mission
to block Separatist annexation</i>

25
00:00:36,290 --> 00:00:37,625
<i>of the Qiilura system,</i>

26
00:00:37,667 --> 00:00:41,170
<i>is waylaid to provide desperately
needed humanitarian relief</i>

27
00:00:41,254 --> 00:00:43,881
<i>to the people on the surface of Aleen.</i>

28
00:00:46,467 --> 00:00:48,970
<i>Commander Wolff e,
we've been waiting for your report.</i>

29
00:00:49,053 --> 00:00:52,974
We've located clusters of life forms
on the planet's surface, Senator.

30
00:00:53,599 --> 00:00:55,309
There are thousands of survivors.

31
00:00:55,643 --> 00:00:57,144
<i>That is good news.</i>

32
00:00:57,186 --> 00:00:59,313
<i>The Aleena will be very glad to see you.</i>

33
00:00:59,355 --> 00:01:04,652
Yes, well, my orders are to get them
on the path to rebuilding and move on.

34
00:01:04,694 --> 00:01:07,530
General Plo needs reinforcements
as soon as possible.

35
00:01:07,613 --> 00:01:09,323
<i>Your orders stand.</i>

36
00:01:09,407 --> 00:01:12,994
<i>With hope leave them,
but return to the war you must.</i>

37
00:01:13,077 --> 00:01:16,080
Yes, sir. We'll start landing
procedures immediately.

38
00:01:59,123 --> 00:02:01,709
Huh, really? Must you be so rough?

39
00:02:01,876 --> 00:02:05,379
What, you think this is rough?
Wait till we get to the surface.

40
00:02:05,421 --> 00:02:09,008
Traipsing through a natural disaster zone
is not my kind of diversion, Artoo.

41
00:02:10,509 --> 00:02:13,721
You may be game for adventure.
I certainly am not.

42
00:02:13,763 --> 00:02:15,598
-Oh !
-Suck it up, Shiney.

43
00:02:15,848 --> 00:02:17,058
That will leave a mark.

44
00:02:37,787 --> 00:02:40,998
Great, it's gonna be another one
of those planets.

45
00:03:15,866 --> 00:03:19,286
Okay. Who packed the translator droid?

46
00:03:19,412 --> 00:03:22,289
Hello. Hello. I'm here, Commander.

47
00:03:23,374 --> 00:03:24,875
Oh, hello.

48
00:03:30,214 --> 00:03:33,968
My, a local custom, I suppose. Interesting.

49
00:03:40,141 --> 00:03:43,811
-Ah, did you get that?
-Certainly, I did.

50
00:03:43,853 --> 00:03:48,524
Commander Wolff e, you have the honor
of meeting King Manchucho.

51
00:03:49,024 --> 00:03:50,901
His message, simply put is,

52
00:03:50,985 --> 00:03:54,196
"Welcome to our disaster.
Glad you could come."

53
00:04:01,245 --> 00:04:03,789
They will save us and feed our stomachs.

54
00:04:03,831 --> 00:04:06,834
The Gods below
will know peace once more.

55
00:04:08,794 --> 00:04:11,088
They are expressing gratitude, Commander,

56
00:04:11,172 --> 00:04:15,384
and the chant is a rather flowery way
of asking, "What's for dinner?"

57
00:04:15,468 --> 00:04:16,469
Oh, oh.

58
00:04:17,303 --> 00:04:20,181
<i>Commander, we're experiencing
some settling from the original event.</i>

59
00:04:20,514 --> 00:04:21,891
<i>It's to be expected.</i>

60
00:04:21,974 --> 00:04:23,684
An aftershock, everyone.

61
00:04:23,768 --> 00:04:26,520
No, no. Please remain calm. I repeat.

62
00:04:33,986 --> 00:04:36,322
Well. Yes, yes. Yes, thank you.

63
00:04:36,489 --> 00:04:39,825
It wasn't actually me,
but thank you anyway.

64
00:04:40,284 --> 00:04:44,455
Trooper squads, scan for unstable ground.
Mark unsafe areas.

65
00:04:44,538 --> 00:04:46,665
Let's get these cans unloaded.

66
00:04:51,754 --> 00:04:54,882
Access and repair
of their mainframe computers is job one.

67
00:04:54,965 --> 00:04:57,760
The R2-unit has uploaded
the Republic's reboot manuals

68
00:04:57,885 --> 00:05:01,555
with instructions on how to make
the equipment we're leaving operational.

69
00:05:20,074 --> 00:05:23,744
They are asking if we would
"Make peace in the ground."

70
00:05:24,453 --> 00:05:26,539
We're good, but not that good.

71
00:05:26,580 --> 00:05:28,165
-Sinker!
-Commander.

72
00:05:28,249 --> 00:05:29,834
Take your team, the R2-unit

73
00:05:29,917 --> 00:05:31,919
and a couple of Aleena
to the mainframe station.

74
00:05:32,002 --> 00:05:33,379
Let's get them back online.

75
00:05:33,420 --> 00:05:34,755
On it, sir.

76
00:05:34,839 --> 00:05:36,215
All right, little fellas, let's go.

77
00:05:50,104 --> 00:05:52,147
Looks like the rubble is blocking the entry.

78
00:05:52,231 --> 00:05:53,440
I got this.

79
00:05:53,482 --> 00:05:54,900
Whoa, whoa, whoa, Boost,

80
00:05:54,942 --> 00:05:57,444
you want what's left of the place
crashing down on our heads?

81
00:05:57,570 --> 00:05:59,738
You worry too much.

82
00:06:03,492 --> 00:06:05,286
I could've done that!

83
00:06:10,207 --> 00:06:12,084
After you, little guy.

84
00:06:24,847 --> 00:06:27,141
Run metrics on structural degradation,
will you?

85
00:06:31,812 --> 00:06:32,980
Did you find anything?

86
00:06:34,732 --> 00:06:37,568
All right, let's get the download started.

87
00:06:50,873 --> 00:06:54,376
Another quake?
Coming here was a bad idea.

88
00:06:54,793 --> 00:06:57,129
I'm beginning to agree with you.

89
00:07:08,015 --> 00:07:10,517
We've marked out areas
for a temporary hospital

90
00:07:10,935 --> 00:07:12,686
and a communal kitchen here.

91
00:07:24,531 --> 00:07:26,492
The Aleena feel great shame.

92
00:07:26,825 --> 00:07:29,870
He is saying, first, peace must be restored.

93
00:07:30,329 --> 00:07:33,040
We must go inside...

94
00:07:33,082 --> 00:07:34,708
Under... Inside.

95
00:07:35,876 --> 00:07:38,087
He says no to the kitchen.

96
00:07:38,379 --> 00:07:40,172
This is a relief mission.

97
00:07:40,506 --> 00:07:44,510
Indeed.
Perhaps, they do not allow eating in public.

98
00:07:51,058 --> 00:07:52,601
Do I need this?

99
00:07:57,898 --> 00:07:58,899
Here's how it is.

100
00:07:59,024 --> 00:08:00,818
My orders are to deliver supplies

101
00:08:00,901 --> 00:08:03,570
and reestablish power
and communication systems.

102
00:08:03,654 --> 00:08:04,780
Report back to the transport

103
00:08:04,863 --> 00:08:08,575
the moment
that R2-unit has completed the download.

104
00:08:08,909 --> 00:08:11,412
Tell them we'll be out of their hair
in no time.

105
00:08:11,578 --> 00:08:13,539
Splendid. A firm hand.

106
00:08:13,580 --> 00:08:16,583
Well done, Commander, if I may say.
Well done.

107
00:08:21,672 --> 00:08:23,257
Download in progress, Commander.

108
00:08:23,632 --> 00:08:25,968
<i>Excellent. Report back to the staging area.</i>

109
00:08:26,093 --> 00:08:28,971
<i>We need all hands on deck.
The droid can finish up.</i>

110
00:08:29,096 --> 00:08:33,183
On our way, sir. All right, Artoo,
stay here and monitor the download

111
00:08:33,267 --> 00:08:34,768
and get back to the ship
as soon as possible.

112
00:08:38,939 --> 00:08:40,149
Watch your step, Shiney.

113
00:08:40,232 --> 00:08:41,900
Impossible clones.

114
00:08:46,113 --> 00:08:47,990
Hello. What have we here?

115
00:08:51,118 --> 00:08:52,411
Something to show us?

116
00:08:52,453 --> 00:08:56,248
I see no reason why not,
time permitting, of course.

117
00:08:58,625 --> 00:09:00,586
Rather impatient creatures, aren't they?

118
00:09:02,171 --> 00:09:04,465
A little diplomacy goes a long way.

119
00:09:04,548 --> 00:09:06,008
Of course you wouldn't understand.

120
00:09:06,091 --> 00:09:08,385
But there is no harm in humoring them.

121
00:09:14,308 --> 00:09:16,977
Yes, yes, yes, we're coming. We're coming.

122
00:09:20,147 --> 00:09:23,484
Artoo, keep your sensor on them,
just in case.

123
00:09:26,862 --> 00:09:28,489
Oh, my!

124
00:09:35,746 --> 00:09:37,664
Oh, yes, I see.

125
00:09:37,706 --> 00:09:40,292
A sacred treasure indeed,

126
00:09:40,334 --> 00:09:44,338
to be excavated and examined
at a later stage with the proper equipment.

127
00:09:48,592 --> 00:09:51,011
Better to stay at a safe distance, thank you.

128
00:10:02,356 --> 00:10:04,233
I have a bad feeling about this.

129
00:10:04,650 --> 00:10:08,028
Artoo!

130
00:10:16,954 --> 00:10:19,206
Artoo, is that you?

131
00:10:23,335 --> 00:10:25,921
I suppose that could have been worse.

132
00:10:32,302 --> 00:10:33,512
Oh, my!

133
00:10:36,223 --> 00:10:37,558
Now, it is.

134
00:10:40,227 --> 00:10:42,729
There must be some way out of here.

135
00:10:58,162 --> 00:11:01,165
Setting foot on this planet
was a mistake in the first place.

136
00:11:01,248 --> 00:11:03,584
We belong on Senator Amidala's balcony,

137
00:11:03,667 --> 00:11:07,921
watching Coruscant's glorious moons
rise above the City of Spires...

138
00:11:09,256 --> 00:11:11,091
What was that?

139
00:11:11,175 --> 00:11:13,427
Wait, no. Shut... Shut it off.

140
00:11:15,929 --> 00:11:18,599
Daylight. We're saved.

141
00:11:18,682 --> 00:11:20,934
I knew I would find a way out.

142
00:11:48,962 --> 00:11:51,465
Look, little guy,
we're doing everything we can.

143
00:11:51,757 --> 00:11:54,051
Has anyone seen the translator droid?

144
00:11:55,677 --> 00:11:58,305
Okay. That's fine with me. Whatever.

145
00:12:05,938 --> 00:12:07,564
Did you see that?

146
00:12:10,859 --> 00:12:12,945
It's an ambush. We're under attack.

147
00:12:12,986 --> 00:12:14,988
Get these bugs off. Get off!

148
00:12:15,113 --> 00:12:16,365
Artoo, help!

149
00:12:16,490 --> 00:12:19,660
Okay. Stop! Stop!
Okay, that's quite enough.

150
00:12:19,826 --> 00:12:22,537
Sometimes, Artoo, you go too far.

151
00:12:22,621 --> 00:12:26,166
Why have you come?

152
00:12:28,126 --> 00:12:31,630
I believe this tree is talking to us.

153
00:12:37,302 --> 00:12:40,430
You do not belong.

154
00:12:40,889 --> 00:12:44,351
I heartily agree.
Being here is a terrible mistake.

155
00:12:45,018 --> 00:12:49,356
Go! Leave us to rest!

156
00:12:50,023 --> 00:12:51,692
We will be happily on our way

157
00:12:51,733 --> 00:12:54,444
if you would just point us
in the right direction.

158
00:12:54,903 --> 00:13:01,576
Why have the surface dwellers
destroyed the peace?

159
00:13:02,703 --> 00:13:05,455
To be accurate, the quakes did that.

160
00:13:06,039 --> 00:13:09,126
The ground shakes

161
00:13:09,543 --> 00:13:13,046
to keep out their foul air,

162
00:13:13,505 --> 00:13:18,218
which poisons and destroys us.

163
00:13:19,261 --> 00:13:21,805
The quakes have caused many to die,

164
00:13:21,888 --> 00:13:24,224
that is why we have come to help.

165
00:13:24,266 --> 00:13:25,934
How?

166
00:13:26,018 --> 00:13:27,477
However we can.

167
00:13:27,561 --> 00:13:30,939
There is not much time.

168
00:13:31,023 --> 00:13:35,068
Find what you were sent here to do.

169
00:13:35,193 --> 00:13:37,654
Ask Orphne.

170
00:13:37,738 --> 00:13:39,323
She will know.

171
00:13:39,406 --> 00:13:43,076
Yes, yes, yes,
on our way to see Orphne directly.

172
00:13:43,160 --> 00:13:45,370
Artoo, let's get out of here.

173
00:14:19,237 --> 00:14:22,074
My ocular sensors
seem to be malfunctioning.

174
00:14:23,241 --> 00:14:24,826
Certainly, I remember.

175
00:14:24,910 --> 00:14:27,871
He said the surface dwellers
destroyed the peace.

176
00:14:29,081 --> 00:14:32,292
I don't know. Look, let's find this Orphne.

177
00:14:32,626 --> 00:14:35,045
It seems she has all the answers.

178
00:14:36,338 --> 00:14:38,090
Oh, my...

179
00:15:02,280 --> 00:15:03,824
Pardon me, madam.

180
00:15:06,660 --> 00:15:07,661
Oh...

181
00:15:07,911 --> 00:15:09,871
I can't eat you.

182
00:15:10,288 --> 00:15:12,207
Well, that's a relief.

183
00:15:12,290 --> 00:15:15,127
If you are Orphne, we have come to ask...

184
00:15:15,168 --> 00:15:16,670
How to get back?

185
00:15:16,753 --> 00:15:19,923
Well, yes. We have lost our way.

186
00:15:20,048 --> 00:15:22,134
There is a covenant

187
00:15:22,175 --> 00:15:27,431
between the Aleena of old
and our subterranean world.

188
00:15:27,639 --> 00:15:32,394
We survive
because the ground keeps us apart.

189
00:15:32,477 --> 00:15:33,520
But you are apart.

190
00:15:33,603 --> 00:15:37,315
No. The divide was breached

191
00:15:37,357 --> 00:15:40,902
when they attacked our most sacred site.

192
00:15:41,027 --> 00:15:42,112
Attacked?

193
00:15:42,195 --> 00:15:46,366
Without going through
the natural filtering process,

194
00:15:46,450 --> 00:15:50,495
the surface air is deadly to us.

195
00:15:50,537 --> 00:15:53,248
We caused the quakes that followed.

196
00:15:53,331 --> 00:15:56,460
But so many on the surface have died.

197
00:15:56,543 --> 00:15:59,629
We are not destroyers by nature,

198
00:15:59,713 --> 00:16:04,342
but we must do what is in our power
to seal the breach.

199
00:16:04,634 --> 00:16:07,262
We can seal the breach,
just tell us where it is.

200
00:16:07,345 --> 00:16:08,555
We can help.

201
00:16:09,139 --> 00:16:13,101
If you have come to help us, you will help.

202
00:16:13,185 --> 00:16:18,815
If you are meant to return to the surface,
you will find your way.

203
00:16:18,899 --> 00:16:21,568
What? But this is a dead end.

204
00:16:23,487 --> 00:16:26,406
You can't keep us here. This is an outrage.

205
00:16:26,698 --> 00:16:30,243
Your destiny is your own.

206
00:16:30,285 --> 00:16:33,914
Perhaps it is through your desire to survive

207
00:16:33,997 --> 00:16:37,834
that your greater purpose will be revealed.

208
00:16:38,710 --> 00:16:41,755
You can run, but cannot walk.

209
00:16:41,838 --> 00:16:45,509
You have a mouth, but cannot talk.

210
00:16:45,592 --> 00:16:48,553
You have a head, but never weep.

211
00:16:48,595 --> 00:16:52,516
You have a bed, but never sleep.

212
00:16:52,599 --> 00:16:56,603
Ask yourself, who are you?

213
00:16:57,771 --> 00:16:59,940
Wait. Wait, Orphne! Don't go!

214
00:17:03,818 --> 00:17:06,238
Artoo, we're doomed.

215
00:17:06,279 --> 00:17:08,949
I don't know.

216
00:17:09,074 --> 00:17:10,742
What was the breach that she spoke of?

217
00:17:10,784 --> 00:17:12,619
What was broken?

218
00:17:12,786 --> 00:17:15,622
Artoo, hurry, replay Orphne's message.

219
00:17:16,456 --> 00:17:18,708
Yes, riddle. I know it's a riddle.

220
00:17:18,792 --> 00:17:22,337
That's what we're trying to figure out,
what the riddle means.

221
00:17:22,420 --> 00:17:23,922
Just play it back, would you?

222
00:17:24,464 --> 00:17:27,467
<i>You can run, but cannot walk.</i>

223
00:17:27,509 --> 00:17:31,221
<i>You have a mouth, but cannot talk.</i>

224
00:17:31,304 --> 00:17:34,224
<i>You have a head, but never weep.</i>

225
00:17:34,307 --> 00:17:37,811
<i>You have a bed, but never sleep.</i>

226
00:17:38,270 --> 00:17:40,564
Run, but cannot walk. Yes.

227
00:17:41,231 --> 00:17:44,526
Have a mouth, but cannot talk. Hmm.

228
00:17:46,653 --> 00:17:49,322
Don't worry, Artoo,
I'll figure it out very soon.

229
00:17:49,614 --> 00:17:51,241
Riddles are my specialty.

230
00:17:51,324 --> 00:17:55,662
Let's see. Cannot walk.
A mouth, but cannot talk.

231
00:17:58,498 --> 00:17:59,666
What? Fire?

232
00:17:59,791 --> 00:18:02,168
It isn't fire. Let me think.

233
00:18:07,090 --> 00:18:08,174
Soil?

234
00:18:08,592 --> 00:18:10,719
Of course it's not soil!

235
00:18:10,802 --> 00:18:13,972
What are you going on about?
I nearly had it.

236
00:18:14,347 --> 00:18:18,101
Water? Artoo, will you stop your mumbling
and let me think.

237
00:18:19,102 --> 00:18:21,813
What are you doing now?
This is no time to clean up.

238
00:18:21,855 --> 00:18:25,025
All this water. I detest getting wet!

239
00:18:28,486 --> 00:18:30,447
Water. Water.

240
00:18:30,530 --> 00:18:35,285
A river. A river! Artoo, it's a river!
That's it, I have figured it out.

241
00:18:35,368 --> 00:18:38,622
It is a river. River is the magic word.

242
00:18:39,914 --> 00:18:42,042
Look, it's working!

243
00:18:42,125 --> 00:18:45,211
Oh, quick, Artoo, quick.
This might be our ticket out of here.

244
00:18:46,129 --> 00:18:47,297
You've figured it out?

245
00:18:47,922 --> 00:18:49,549
How could you...

246
00:19:17,285 --> 00:19:18,620
Artoo, we've made it!

247
00:19:18,703 --> 00:19:20,080
We're saved!

248
00:19:25,377 --> 00:19:27,587
Oh, my! The vapors!

249
00:19:27,629 --> 00:19:29,589
Look, Artoo. Do you see?

250
00:19:31,424 --> 00:19:33,593
That is why the Aleena
cannot seal the breach,

251
00:19:33,677 --> 00:19:37,847
the air below the ground is deadly to them,
but it has no effect on us.

252
00:19:37,931 --> 00:19:40,767
I understand, Artoo. I finally understand!

253
00:19:40,850 --> 00:19:42,936
They are waiting for us to help them.

254
00:19:43,353 --> 00:19:44,771
They need us.

255
00:19:50,276 --> 00:19:52,362
We must do what we should have done
in the first place.

256
00:19:52,445 --> 00:19:55,115
We must block the hole
which leads to the underworld

257
00:19:55,198 --> 00:19:57,242
using that seal.

258
00:19:57,283 --> 00:19:59,703
That is the breach that Orphne spoke of.

259
00:20:03,456 --> 00:20:05,458
Go, Artoo! You can do it!

260
00:20:06,710 --> 00:20:08,962
What do you mean I have to help?

261
00:20:09,045 --> 00:20:11,089
No, you are right, Artoo.

262
00:20:20,890 --> 00:20:25,311
Oh, oh, oh ! You are welcome.
I knew we would be able to help.

263
00:20:25,395 --> 00:20:28,940
Hey, Shiney! You two finished with those
repairs on the computer system?

264
00:20:29,441 --> 00:20:34,028
My good sir, you may not realize it,
but we have been on quite an adventure.

265
00:20:34,320 --> 00:20:36,489
Really? Quite an adventure, huh?

266
00:20:36,573 --> 00:20:37,866
Get a load of this one.

267
00:20:38,158 --> 00:20:40,493
One? Which one? What... What do you...

268
00:20:40,535 --> 00:20:42,829
Just come on,
the Commander's been looking for you.

269
00:21:00,805 --> 00:21:03,349
You are most welcome, Your Majesty.

270
00:21:03,433 --> 00:21:06,644
Just doing our job
in the service of the Republic.

271
00:21:25,038 --> 00:21:29,250
No, Artoo, I will tell the story.
No one understands you, anyway.

272
00:21:30,502 --> 00:21:32,045
It's only proper.

273
00:21:32,128 --> 00:21:33,922
I am the one who solved the riddle,

274
00:21:34,005 --> 00:21:36,716
I should be the one to relay the story.

275
00:21:36,841 --> 00:21:40,553
I will, of course,
report on your individual heroics.

276
00:21:40,595 --> 00:21:42,555
Do you think Senator Amidala will hold...

277
00:21:42,639 --> 00:21:45,475
As soon as we rendezvous
with Master Gallia,

278
00:21:45,558 --> 00:21:46,893
we're off-loading those two.

279
00:21:46,935 --> 00:21:49,062
I couldn't agree more, sir.

280
00:21:49,145 --> 00:21:50,396
...himself shall attend.

281
00:21:50,563 --> 00:21:52,732
Dare to dream, Artoo. Dare to dream!

282
00:21:56,635 --> 00:22:01,635
http://hiqve.com/

